# BdApiUtil.sys ![:inline](/images/twitter_verified.png) 

### Description

Driver can be used to load unsigned drivers. IOCTL code which takes a PID and terminates it (arbitrary process termination). Admin privileges required to install the driver, but if it&#39;s already installed, can be called by any user (non admin).
- **UUID**: 708650ed-c497-48be-97bc-9edd48cf2a1a
- **Created**: 2025-12-09
- **Author**: christopher-ellis-workday, plisskien, Julian Pena

{{< button "https://github.com/magicsword-io/LOLDrivers/raw/main/drivers/29e1264dd642b646fbef9bd347b1b860.bin" "Download" >}}{{< button "https://www.magicsword.io/premium" "Block" "red" >}}
{{< tip "warning" >}}
This download link contains the vulnerable driver!

{{< /tip >}}

### Commands

```
sc.exe create BdApiUtil.sys binPath=C:\windows\temp\BdApiUtil.sys type=kernel &amp;&amp; sc.exe start BdApiUtil.sys
```


| Use Case | Privileges | Operating System | 
|:---- | ---- | ---- |
| Elevate privileges | kernel | Windows 10 |
